# ppp
(speed.cam = as.ppp(speed_cameras)) # (speed.cam = as.ppp(st_geometry(speed_cameras)))
## Warning in as.ppp.sf(speed_cameras): only first attribute column is used for marks
## Marked planar point pattern: 71 points
## marks are numeric, of storage type  'integer'
## window: rectangle = [9893.58, 46963.78] x [30183.76, 46445.29] units
# Boundary
sg_regions = st_read("MP14_PLNG_AREA_WEB_PL.shp") # sg regions
## Reading layer `MP14_PLNG_AREA_WEB_PL' from data source 
##   `/Users/ch0002techvc/Downloads/EC627 Spatial Econometrics & Data Analysis/MP14_PLNG_AREA_WEB_PL.shp' 
##   using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 55 features and 12 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: 2667.538 ymin: 15748.72 xmax: 56396.44 ymax: 50256.33
## Projected CRS: SVY21
sg_regions = st_make_valid(sg_regions); table(st_is_valid(sg_regions))
## 
## TRUE 
##   55
isTRUE(all.equal(st_crs(sg_regions), st_crs(speed_cameras)))
## [1] TRUE
sg = st_union(sg_regions)

# owin
(sg.owin = as.owin(sg))
## window: polygonal boundary
## enclosing rectangle: [2667.54, 56396.44] x [15748.72, 50256.33] units
Window(speed.cam) = sg.owin
speed.cam
## Marked planar point pattern: 71 points
## marks are numeric, of storage type  'integer'
## window: polygonal boundary
## enclosing rectangle: [2667.54, 56396.44] x [15748.72, 50256.33] units
plot(speed.cam)

# re-assign marks
marks(speed.cam) = as.factor(speed_cameras$TYPE) # categorical marks must be given as factor.
plot(speed.cam)

################################################################################

## Alternative approach
XY = st_coordinates(speed_cameras)
(speed.cam2 = ppp(XY[,1], XY[,2], window = sg.owin,
                 marks = as.factor(speed_cameras$TYPE)))
## Warning: data contain duplicated points
## Marked planar point pattern: 71 points
## Multitype, with levels = Fixed, Laser, Mobile 
## window: polygonal boundary
## enclosing rectangle: [2667.54, 56396.44] x [15748.72, 50256.33] units
plot(speed.cam2)

duplicated(speed.cam2)
##  [1] FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE
## [16] FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE
## [31] FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE
## [46] FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE  TRUE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE
## [61] FALSE FALSE  TRUE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE
# What to do about duplicated entries?

# 1. Discard duplicated points
(speed.cam3 = unique(speed.cam2))
## Marked planar point pattern: 69 points
## Multitype, with levels = Fixed, Laser, Mobile 
## window: polygonal boundary
## enclosing rectangle: [2667.54, 56396.44] x [15748.72, 50256.33] units
plot(speed.cam3)

# 2. Perturb coordinates slightly
(speed.cam4 = rjitter(speed.cam2, retry=T))
## Marked planar point pattern: 71 points
## Multitype, with levels = Fixed, Laser, Mobile 
## window: polygonal boundary
## enclosing rectangle: [2667.54, 56396.44] x [15748.72, 50256.33] units
plot(speed.cam4)

# 3. Make the points of the pattern unique and attach the multiplicities of the points to the pattern as marks.
marks(speed.cam2) = data.frame(type=marks(speed.cam2), mul=multiplicity(speed.cam2))
(speed.cam5 = unique(speed.cam2))
## Marked planar point pattern: 69 points
## Mark variables: type, mul 
## window: polygonal boundary
## enclosing rectangle: [2667.54, 56396.44] x [15748.72, 50256.33] units
plot(speed.cam5)

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plot(speed.cam2)
plot(speed.cam3)
plot(speed.cam4)
plot(speed.cam5)

par(mfrow=c(1,1))
